summary:
**Material Information Summary:**  

- **Temporary Port Disruption:**  
  - Crane failure at Port of Broome (29 June 2025) deferred ~41,000 tonnes of concentrate shipments (June 2025 quarter).  
  - Operations expected to resume "in the coming days."  

- **June 2025 Quarter Performance:**  
  - Record mining: 2.8Mt total, including 1Mt in June.  
  - Production: ~150,000t ilmenite, ~40,000t zircon concentrate.  
  - Shipments: 201,000t total (162,000t ilmenite, 38,000t zircon) – below expectations due to port disruption.  

*(Note: Other sections are background/boilerplate; no additional material details.)*
